During the process, ideas were collected under three meta-topics or campaigns: governance, communication and conflicts in the homeownersâ€™ association.

Participation

From the 362 users registered as participants, 155 (42.8%) have actually contributed to at least one of the campaigns in some way, i.e., submitting ideas, placing comments and/or voting, while 207 (57.2%) only observed the activity.

Most of the content was generated by 56 participants (15.5% of the 362), who have actively taken part in the process by posting ideas, and placing comments and voting, i.e., generated the three type of content. The remaining 99 (27.3%) participants contributed with some additional ideas, comments, and votes.

Out of the 155 contributors, 56 (36.1%) have generated the three type of content (ideas, votes, and comments), 20 (12.9%) have submitted ideas and posted votes but not comments, and 79 (51%) have contributed by only commenting on the existing ideas.

Only 30 participants have contributed with ideas, comments and votes on each of three campaings, 48 have participated only in the communication and governance campaigns, 34 have produced content for the communication and conflicts in the homeownersâ€™ association campaigns, and 47 have taken part just campaigns related with governance and conflicts between homeowners. The most â€œattractiveâ€ campaign was the related with the governance laws with 103 participants; between the other two, the campaign related with conflicts between homeowners had 82 contributors while the one in charge of collecting ideas regarding communication attracted 69 participants.
